body:
## Problem

**Same bug class as #1189 (vs comparison pages schema SSR fix) — now affecting 157 lick pages.**

The `generateLickSchema()` function in `App.js` emits a rich `@graph` with:
- `VideoObject` (YouTube embed)
- `HowTo` (step-by-step breakdown)
- `MusicRecording` (song metadata)
- `BreadcrumbList` (navigation)

But `App.js` runs **client-side only**. Googlebot and all AI crawlers receive the SSR HTML from `api/meta/[...path].js`, which for lick pages (line 589-601) returns ONLY title + description — **zero JSON-LD**.

```javascript
// api/meta/[...path].js:589 — lick handler (CURRENT — no articleSchema)
return {
  title: `${lick.name} — ${lick.drummerName} Drum Lick | ${SITE_NAME}`,
  description: ...,
  type: 'article',
  url: ...,
  // ← NO articleSchema, so generateArticleSchema() emits nothing
};
```

## Impact

157 lick pages (63 drummers × ~2-3 licks each) have rich schema that crawlers **cannot see**. This blocks HowTo rich results, VideoObject video carousels, and MusicRecording AI citations on ALL lick pages.

## Fix

Add `articleSchema` to the lick page SSR handler in `api/meta/[...path].js:589`:

```javascript
const lickPageMatch = path.match(/^\/drummers\/([a-z0-9-]+)\/licks\/([a-z0-9-]+)$/);
if (lickPageMatch) {
  const [, drummerSlug, lickSlug] = lickPageMatch;
  const lick = SIGNATURE_LICKS[lickSlug];
  if (lick) {
    return {
      title: `${lick.name} — ${lick.drummerName} (${lick.band}) Drum Lick | ${SITE_NAME}`,
      description: ...,
      type: 'article',
      url: ...,
      articleSchema: JSON.stringify({
        '@context': 'https://schema.org',
        '@graph': [
          {
            '@type': 'HowTo',
            name: lick.name,
            description: lick.description,
            // steps from lick.steps if available
          },
          {
            '@type': 'VideoObject',
            name: lick.name,
            description: lick.description,
            thumbnailUrl: `https://img.youtube.com/vi/${lick.youtubeId}/maxresdefault.jpg`,
            embedUrl: `https://www.youtube.com/embed/${lick.youtubeId}`,
          },
          {
            '@type': 'MusicRecording',
            name: lick.song,
            byArtist: { '@type': 'MusicGroup', name: lick.band },
            inAlbum: { '@type': 'MusicAlbum', name: lick.album },
          }
        ]
      }),
      breadcrumbSchema: [
        { name: 'Home', url: BASE_URL },
        { name: lick.drummerName, url: `${BASE_URL}/${drummerSlug}` },
        { name: 'Signature Licks', url: `${BASE_URL}/drummers/${drummerSlug}/licks` },
        { name: lick.name, url: `${BASE_URL}/drummers/${drummerSlug}/licks/${lickSlug}` },
      ],
    };
  }
}
```

## Files to Touch

- `api/meta/[...path].js` — lick page handler at line ~589

## Quality Gate

- `curl -s https://metalforge.io/api/meta/drummers/george-kollias/licks/god-of-the-mind | jq '.articleSchema'` → returns non-null JSON
- JSON-LD type is `@graph` array containing HowTo + VideoObject + MusicRecording
- BreadcrumbList is populated with correct 4-level hierarchy

## Estimated Uplift

Unlocks HowTo rich results + VideoObject video carousels on 157 lick pages. Directly serves "how to play [drummer] lick" AI Overview queries. Same pattern as the /vs schema fix (#1189) which shipped and confirmed the approach.

## Done

- [x] SSR meta handler emits JSON-LD for all 157 lick pages
- [x] HowTo, VideoObject, MusicRecording types all present in SSR response
- [x] BreadcrumbList emitted in SSR
